fields.taste: Pleasant, resinous hop aroma with hints of citrus (orange) and herbal flavors. A high alpha hop with balanced bitterness and an acceptable aroma profile; a versatile replacement for both high alpha and dual purpose varieties
fields.name: Admiral

fields.taste: Floral, earthy, citrus and grapefruit tones
fields.name: Ahtanum

fields.taste: Floral, tropical, and citrus (lemon, orange and grapefruit) characteristics
fields.name: Amarillo

fields.taste: Very fine spice and herbal notes with subtle citrus characteristics. Closely resembling Strisselspalt, but with higher oil and alpha content
fields.name: Aramis

fields.taste: Mild floral and spicy characteristics with slightly grassy overtones. Excellent for finishing and dry hopping
fields.name: Boadicea

fields.taste: Strong spice, blackcurrant, loganberry and lemon characteristics. Often used in traditional cask conditioned beers due to its distinct characteristics
fields.name: Bramling Cross

fields.taste: Spicy, fruity characteristics, black currant
fields.name: Brewer's Gold

fields.taste: Black currant, fruit and spice characteristics. Has a high resin content and gives a well-balanced bitterness which is ideally complimented by late hop additions in lager beers
fields.name: Brewer's Gold (Dld)

fields.taste: Strong and zesty blackcurrant characteristics
fields.name: Bullion

fields.taste: Medium intense floral, citrus and grapefruit tones
fields.name: Cascade

fields.taste: Mild herbal aroma with strong melon, lemon, lime and slightly spicy notes.
fields.name: Cashmere

fields.taste: Medium intensity floral and citrus (lemon) tones. Very balanced, sometimes called a super Cascade
fields.name: Centennial

fields.taste: Cedar, green tea and sweet floral characteristics (as a late addition, it can provide crisp, fruity flavors). A versatile hop, widely used for both early and late kettle additions
fields.name: Challenger

fields.taste: Mild floral and citrus characteristics. Similar to Galena but with higher alpha acids
fields.name: Chelan

fields.taste: Distinct, medium intensity spice and pine characteristics with subtle notes of grapefruit.A high alpha hop with acceptable aroma
fields.name: Chinook

fields.taste: Strong citrus and tropical tones of grapefruit, melon, lime, gooseberry, passion fruit and lychee. One of the most popular new varieties, known for its intense flavor and aroma characteristics
fields.name: Citra

fields.taste: Strong floral and spicy characteristics. Excellent general purpose variety with balanced bittering and aroma potential
fields.name: Cluster

fields.taste: Subtle earth and mild fruit tones. Aroma characteristics are similar to Fuggle
fields.name: Columbia

fields.taste: Pungent, black pepper, licorice characteristics with subtle citrus overtones. Excellent for dry hopping
fields.name: Columbus

fields.taste: A pungent, wild American aroma with citrus (grapefruit) flavors. Contains a "wild American" aroma that can be objectionable to some brewers
fields.name: Comet

fields.taste: Mild, spicy and floral
fields.name: Crystal

fields.taste: Fresh citrus peel, pine and lemongrass flavors.Delivers a crisp, bitter edge with fine aroma characteristics; often used to balance regional ales and lagers. Works well in single hopped beers and with multiple aroma varieties.
fields.name: Dr. Rudi

fields.taste: Smooth and delicate with floral, lavender, spice, honey, earth, lemon and thyme overtones. A traditional English hop that has been used in kettle and dry hopping
fields.name: East Kent Golding

fields.taste: Spicy, hoppy and floral with hints of anise
fields.name: Ella

fields.taste: Forward fruit flavors. A suitable hop variety for dark beers and American-style Ales
fields.name: Eroica

fields.taste: Distinct tropical, floral, lemon and grapefruit characteristics. An excellent complement to many IPA and Pale Ale oriented hop varieties
fields.name: Falconer's Flight

fields.taste: Strong fruit and citrus characteristics, with layers of spicy and earthy overtones
fields.name: Falconer's Flight 7C's

fields.taste: Slightly spicy, but smooth, with tangerine, orange marmalade, magnolia and floral flavors. A versatile variety perfect for modern beer styles
fields.name: First Gold

fields.taste: Mild wood and fruit characteristics. A traditional English-type variety
fields.name: Fuggle

fields.taste: Delicate and pleasant mint, grass and floral tones. The most revered and famous English hop, known for its full bodied flavor in traditional ales
fields.name: Fuggle (UK)

fields.taste: Typically used as a late addition - the aroma and flavor characteristics become more pronounced the later the addition
fields.name: Galaxy

fields.taste: Spicy, blackcurrant and citrus (grapefruit) tones. Excellent high alpha variety with balanced bittering and aroma characteristics; mainly used for bittering, but finding favor as a dual purpose variety.
fields.name: Galena

fields.taste: Pleasant hop aroma. Excellent dual purpose variety with well balanced bittering properties and a pleasant aroma profile
fields.name: Glacier

fields.taste: Mild and delicate with sweet floral characteristics
fields.name: Golding

fields.taste: Subtle spiciness. Typically used in lagers, but carries the Styrian characteristic of subtle spiciness that is perfect for a stout. Works well when included with finishing varieties such as Fuggle and Willamette
fields.name: Green Bullet

fields.taste: Mild and pleasant, yet spicy, with herbal and floral characteristics
fields.name: Hallertau

fields.taste: Floral and fruity with passion fruit, grapefruit, pineapple, grape and lemongrass overtones  One of several new German varieties with bold flavor profiles, perfect for American-style Ales
fields.name: Hallertau Blanc

fields.taste: Mild, yet spicy, with floral and citrus tones. The classic German aroma hop associated with Bavarian-style lager beers and distinguished by an intense, pleasantly harmonic bitterness
fields.name: Hallertau Mittelfrh

fields.taste: Very mild and pleasant with delicate floral and herbal tones
fields.name: Helga

fields.taste: Spicy, floral and hop notes with hints of pine, black pepper and melon. Imparts robust, hoppy tang flavors
fields.name: Herkules

fields.taste: Mild, herbal and floral characteristics, with fruity overtones. A delicate aroma hop used mainly in lager type beers
fields.name: Hersbruker

fields.taste: Pleasant and spicy, with floral characteristics
fields.name: Horizon

fields.taste: Distinct fruit characteristics including honeydew melon and strawberry flavors. An excellent consideration for varieties not necessarily associated with typical hop flavors
fields.name: Hull Melon

fields.taste: Mild and spicy with subtle lemon and citrus characteristics
fields.name: Liberty

fields.taste: No distinct aroma characteristics.Generally accepted as a clean bittering hop for ales and lagers
fields.name: Magnum

fields.taste: A delicate aroma with inclinations towards floral and fruit flavorings and a prevalent hoppy tang
fields.name: Magnum (Dld)

fields.taste: Distinct tangerine and citrus flavors. Displays a pleasant fruitiness in finished beers
fields.name: Mandarina Bavaria

fields.taste: Fruity, flowery, spiecey (herbs), anise and piney notes. Strong, intense aroma.
fields.name: Marynka

fields.taste: Strong earthy, floral and citrus impressions. High alpha variety with high bitter value, good aroma, strong storage stability and low co-humulone
fields.name: Merkur

fields.taste: Mild and resinous with floral and herbal tones
fields.name: Millennium

fields.taste: A complex array of tropical fruit, citrus, berry, herbal, earthy and pine characteristics.An excellent aroma variety
fields.name: Mosaic

fields.taste: Lively lemon and lime tones with background hints of tropical fruit. An excellent variety for single hop bills with multiple applications
fields.name: Motueka

fields.taste: Mild, herbal and somewhat pungent or spicy. An aroma hop varieties with similarities to the German Hallertau and Hersbrucker varieties
fields.name: Mt. Hood

fields.taste: Excellent floral and noble aromas, with citrus and licorice overtones. Similar to Hallertau but with more bittering strength
fields.name: Mt. Rainier

fields.taste: Distinct cool climate and white wine "fruitiness" with fresh crushed gooseberry and grape infused flavors. An excellent dual purpose hop that can be used to produce a punch or subtle bittering qualities
fields.name: Nelson Sauvin

fields.taste: Viewed as an excllent bittering hop
fields.name: Newport

fields.taste: Pleasant spice, cedar and pine characteristics with hints of floral and berry flavors. An excellent dual purpose hop that works well on its own, or in conjunction with an aroma variety
fields.name: Northdown

fields.taste: Medium intensity, pine and mint characteristics.A true dual purpose hop variety
fields.name: Northern Brewer

fields.taste: Medium intense herbal and floral tones. A true dual purpose hop
fields.name: Northern Brewer (Dld)

fields.taste: Mild and pleasant with spicy, herbal tones.Gaining acceptance as a dual purpose variety
fields.name: Nugget

fields.taste: Citrus characteristics with subtle spicy notes. Typically used as a bittering hop, but containing some citrus and spice characteristics.
fields.name: Olympic

fields.taste: Even dispersal of all aroma characteristics - fruity, floral, herbal and hoppy tones all appear. Good aroma type with average to high bitter value
fields.name: Opal

fields.taste: No distinct characteristics. Some brewers have noted delicate blackberry and floral or oak tones
fields.name: Pacific Gem

fields.taste: Bold herbal aromas with hints of fresh citrus and crushed black pepper
fields.name: Pacific Jade

fields.taste: Classic Hallertau character with some citrus and floral notes. Late additions bring characteristics of orange marmalade, while early additions yield soft, yet solid bittering qualities
fields.name: Pacifica

fields.taste: Apricot, grass and clean floral charcteristics. Used for its aromatic properties and moderate bittering qualities
fields.name: Palisade

fields.taste: Slightly spicy with herbal and floral characteristics
fields.name: Perle

fields.taste: Delicate floral, fruit, spice and mint tones. A highly acceptable aroma variety with balanced bittering characteristics
fields.name: Perle (Dld)

fields.taste: Crisp and mellow tones of pine, chocolate, molasses and spice characteristics. Performs well as a replacement for high alpha or dual purpose hops early in the boil; late hop additions for aroma tend to be mellow
fields.name: Phoenix

fields.taste: Distinct fruit and spice characteristics with pleasant lemon, grapefruit, pear and berry flavors. Often compared to UK Target, Pilgrim performs well as a replacement for high alpha or dual purpose hops
fields.name: Pilgrim

fields.taste: Distinctly hoppy with pleasant citrus (lemon and grapefruit) tones and hints of herbal, cedar flavors. Combines a pleasant aroma with a moderately high alpha acid content
fields.name: Pioneer

fields.taste: Intense floral and pleasant mint tones. A variety with bold taste and differentiating flavor
fields.name: Polaris

fields.taste: Mild aroma typical of classic noble hops
fields.name: Polish Lublin

fields.taste: Pleasant, mild aroma
fields.name: Premiant (CZ)

fields.taste: Pronounced and pleasant, a distinct Australian aroma with cedar, oak and herbal tones
fields.name: Pride of Ringwood

fields.taste: Moderately strong spicy, grassy, floral, mint, earth and honey tones. Originally introduced as a replacement for Fuggle, Progress shows excellent potential at both the start and end of the boil
fields.name: Progress

fields.taste: Fresh orchard fruits, specifically apricot with some resinous pine needle characteristics are noted. Well suited for new world styles where brash fruity character and big, but well constructed bitterness is desired
fields.name: Rakau

fields.taste: Mild spice and earth tones. Features a classic noble aroma, famously used in Pilsners
fields.name: Saaz

fields.taste: Very mild, with pleasant earthy, herbal and floral overtones
fields.name: Saaz (CZ)

fields.taste: Slightly spicy with herbal and floral characteristics
fields.name: Santiam

fields.taste: Distinct spicy, fruit and citrus (tangerine) tones. Good aroma variety with a distinct hoppy tang
fields.name: Saphir

fields.taste: Floral and fruit characteristics
fields.name: Select

fields.taste: Unique passionfruit, pine, earth and citrus characteristics. Known as a bittering hop with a good aroma
fields.name: Simcoe

fields.taste: Fruity flavor profile including hints of peach, grapefruit and passion fruit Balanced bittering
fields.name: Sladek

fields.taste: Predominantly fruity with strong floral and hop tones. A fine aroma variety with high bittering value
fields.name: Smaragd (Emerald)

fields.taste: Unique lemon and dill characteristics. An extremely unique high alpha aroma variety with great bittering characteristics
fields.name: Sorachi Ace

fields.taste: A delicate balance of citrus and spice, including a heady mix of lemon peel and pine needles. Typically used in mainstream lagers, but finding favor in a variety of craft styles
fields.name: Southern Cross

fields.taste: Pleasant but intense fruity flavors with mild floral, grassy, herbal and mint characteristics
fields.name: Sovereign

fields.taste: Mild and herbal, with spicy, floral and fruit tones. Traditional noble aroma hop with average bitter value and pleasant aroma
fields.name: Spalt

fields.taste: Earthy, citrusy aroma
fields.name: Spalter Select

fields.taste: Herbal and spicy, with a hint of floral, citrus (lemon/pineapple) characteristics. Finding favor as a Saaz replacement
fields.name: Sterling

fields.taste: Very fine spicy, herbal, floral, lemon and other fruit tones. Globally accepted as a good aroma hop with similar characteristics to Hersbrucker
fields.name: Strisselpalt

fields.taste: Intense and pleasant displaying floral, pine and hoppy characteristics. Aroma is similar to Styrian Golding, but much lighter with hoppy aroma
fields.name: Styrian Aurora

fields.taste: Intense and pleasant with floral, pine and hop overtones. A world-renowned couplet with moderate bitterness
fields.name: Styrian Bobek

fields.taste: Pleasant and hoppy, similar to traditional European varieties. A quality aroma variety with excellent bitterness and aroma characteristics
fields.name: Styrian Celeia

fields.taste: Very mild, noble hop flavor
fields.name: Styrian Savinjski Golding

fields.taste: Balanced citrus, melon and light apricot tones. Dry hopping displays distinct stone fruit (apricot) and melon characteristics
fields.name: Summer

fields.taste: Distinct spice, earthy, onion, garlic and citrus (pink grapefruit, orange and tangerine) tones. A great late addition hop
fields.name: Summit

fields.taste: Mild and pleasant subtle resin and fruit tones
fields.name: Super Pride

fields.taste: Good, yet delicate, flavor retention
fields.name: Sussex

fields.taste: Complex and subtle, floral and herbal characteristics
fields.name: Sylva

fields.taste: Predominate citrus and lemon notes with cedar, pine, floral, pepper and subtle green melon notes.
fields.name: Tahoma

fields.taste: An excellent bittering hop that tends to be too harsh for aroma purposes late in the boil
fields.name: Target

fields.taste: Strong noble characteristics. A high alpha variety with noble, aromatic, bittering qualities
fields.name: Taurus

fields.taste: Noble aroma that is pleasant and spicy. A true noble aroma variety
fields.name: Tettnang

fields.taste: Mild and pleasant with balanced earthy, herbal and floral aroma impressions. Traditional noble aroma hop
fields.name: Tettnang (Dld)

fields.taste: Resinous, grassy tones with light tropical flavors
fields.name: Topaz

fields.taste: Medium intense floral and herbal (grassy) tones. Imparts beer with a harmonic bitterness
fields.name: Traditon

fields.taste: Pleasant and balanced with notes of melon, orange citrus, resin, spice and pepper.
fields.name: TriplePearl

fields.taste: Strong floral, fruit and citrus characteristics. Contains many of the same characteristics as Strisselspalt, but with a more pronounced flavor profile
fields.name: Triskel

fields.taste: Mild and pleasant with spicy, floral tones. Displays a similar aroma profile to Hallertau mf
fields.name: Ultra

fields.taste: Herbal and floral tones. Similar aroma to Hallertau mf.
fields.name: Vanguard

fields.taste: Intense tangelo and citrus fruit with subtle pine characteristics
fields.name: Waimea

fields.taste: Restrained floral notes and freshly zested lime. Complimented for its rounded flavor, moderate co-humulone, outstanding oil profile and rewarding finish
fields.name: Wakatu

fields.taste: Mild and resinous with subtle citrus, pine and herbal characteristics. Used for its mild, clean bittering properties
fields.name: Warrior

fields.taste: Fresh earthy, botanical and floral flavors. Similar to Goldings, but not as delicate and containing a more robust, hoppy flavor
fields.name: WGV

fields.taste: Mild and pleasant, with slightly spicy and floral tones. A quality aroma hop with low alpha content
fields.name: Willamette

fields.taste: Mild and pleasant. An excellent general purpose variety with smooth bitterness and a pleasant aroma
fields.name: Yakima Gold

fields.taste: Distinct tropical (pineapple) and citrus tones, with slight pine characteristics
fields.name: Zythos
